solution:
We write $-64 = 2^6 \operatorname{cis} 180^\circ,$ so $x^6 = 2^6 \operatorname{cis} 180^\circ.$  The solutions are of the form
\[x = 2 \operatorname{cis} (30^\circ + 60^\circ k),\]where $0 \le k \le 5.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

int i;

draw(Circle((0,0),2));
draw((-2.2,0)--(2.2,0));
draw((0,-2.2)--(0,2.2));

